inn1.comm: and Watson goes first ball! Short rising ball over the stumps, Watson tried to leave it but it bounce much more than he expected and couldn't get the bat out of the way, played it down into the stumps
short and he hops at the crease and clips it to the on side
good delivery and that just leaves the left-hander
drifts wide down the leg side and he is penalised
ends the over with a sharp bouncer, Hughes had to duck quickly to evade it
this was a touch short and wide outside off and Finch doesn't move his feet, slashes away from the body, down to third man
fuller in length outside off and he softly digs it out to the off side
good length outside off and moving away and he stays back and defends
fullish in length outside off and he softly pushes it to the off side
this was a better delivery, coming back in slightly and Hughes decided rather late to leave it
nips back in off the surface and hits him high on the pad and Sammy appeals, perhaps a bit too high
fullish in length outside the off stump and he steers it to the off side
good length outside off and he pushes it to the off side
this was short and had him hopping at the crease to fend it off to the on side

Best gets the openers early! Best's landing the bouncers well this morning, this was directed at Finch's helmet, he couldn't resist the hook, the top edge swirls to fine leg, Narine takes it at the edge of the rope, at first it looked like going all the way
hits a good length outside off and Hughes allows it to go to the keeper
hammers it short of a length and he stays right behind the line to defend
good length and straight and defended solidly back to the bowler
fullish in length outside off and moving away, left alone
slower and left alone to the keeper, Thomas throws it back at the stumps, Marsh a little slow in dragging his feet back
fuller and moving away and he shoulders arms
gets off the mark with a gentle dab down to third man, goes past point
Hughes a bit circumspect there, moves across and gets an inside edge to the pads
rare loose delivery by Best, drifts wide down the leg side
good length outside the off stump and he comes across and defends
first of the morning! Plenty of assurance in that shot, short of a length and moving across, on the backfoot and sliced past backward point
fuller in length and angling across and he doesn't offer a shot
gets across and he decides to let it go to the keeper
149.4 kph, good length on the pads and he works it away down to midwicket for a single
and Hughes still not off the mark, 14  balls now, fuller and angling across and left alone to the keeper
full and angling across and he leaves it alone
watchfully left alone to the keeper, this was closer to the off stump
Marsh flirted with that one, was too late on the shot, the ball was moving across, could have edged that to the slips
outside edge on the drive and well stopped at second slip, fell well short of Bravo
good length on the off stump and punched towards mid-off
stays on the back foot and chops it down towards second slip, it's a maiden
fullish in length outside off and steered to the off side
pacy delivery outside off and left alone to the keeper
147 kph, shorter in length and the batsman does well to get back and across to defend
stays right on the back foot and defends
148 kph, and Hughes finally off the mark after 19 balls! You saw the speed, that was a half volley, leans forward and pushes it through the covers, didn't hit it too hard
150.8 kph! Best cranks up the pace but loses control of it, wide half volley outside off, leans forward and drills it past point and cover
good length on the off stump and he stays back and defends
drifts on the pads and he shuffles and tucks it down to fine leg
good length on the pads and he works it down to fine leg
short and wide outside off and he reaches out and cuts wide of point
good length on the off stump and he goes back and across to defend
goes back and across and works it to the on side
Roach starts off with the bouncer, not his quickest, the batsman ducks under that one
on target this time, short of a length and tucks him up for room, he stays back and defends
139 kph, good length on the off stump and he goes back at the crease and defends
Hughes shuffles across and knocks it to the on side, Roach continues over the wicket
138 kph, short, sharp delivery, hurried onto Hughes who was on the back foot, uneasily fended it off
139 kph, stylishly pulled on one leg by Hughes but it rolls straight to fine leg
stays on the back foot and pushes it to the off side
fuller in length outside off and pushed to the off side
hops on the back foot and uneasily works it to the off side
this was wide outside the off stump, had to really reach out to slash this one down to third man
punches it down to mid-off
skids through and has him in a bit of a tangle, hits him high on the pad and rolls to the off side
short of a length outside off and he punches it just wide of point
looks to work it to the on side but the ball hits him high on the pads and goes to the off side
punches it off the back foot and just beats cover
stands tall and chops it down to point and tells his partner to wait
144 kph, cranking up the pace there, gets on the back foot and defends it down the track
146 kph, even quicker and he is hurried on the back foot, manages to tuck that one away to fine leg
good length on the off stump and defended down the track
stands tall on the toes and he knocks it down to the off side
Hughes cuts that one and Pollard does well at backward point to slide and cut that off
on the pads and he shuffles and clips it to fine leg
good length on the off stump and he stays back and defends
stays back and he comes across and slices it towards point
fullish and moving across and he drives this one crisply but straight to cover
144.8 kph, short of a length and angling towards the off stump and he punches it to Roach's left
145.2 kph, angles across him a bit more and he stays back and slices it to point
wider outside off and plays a flashy square cut that rolls down to third man
140.8 kph, drifts a bit on the pads and he runs it down to fine leg
fullish on the pads and clipped wide of mdwicket
half volley outside the off stump and drives him down to mid-off
on the pads and he sweeps him down to fine leg
tossed up outside off and he defends
beats him! Flight and bounce this time and Marsh was all squared up outside off
goes back and across and whips it to the on side
lovely shot! It was a good length ball a touch wide outside off and he showed the full face and punched it just wide of mid-off and cover, timing and placement perfect
chops it down to point and tells his partner to stay back
144 kph, little shorter in length and he punches it down to mid-on
this was fuller and Hughes misses an opportunity to put that away, flicks it down to midwicket
quite stylish! Hughes plays a Caribbean style pull on one leg, 144 kph, used the pace and ran it down the big gap at deep square leg
short outside off and he dabs it down to point
stays on the back foot and works it to point
Marsh goes for the forceful drive but extra bounce this time beats him
goes back and knocks it back to the bowler
this was short and he mistimes the pull, they risk a single to midwicket but Roach's throw to the keeper is too wide
skids through and he chops it to the off side
gets across and defends this one to the off side
nobody moved! Poor ball from Bravo, half volley wide outside the off stump and he leans forward and crashes that wide of mid-off and cover
good comeback, fires that on a yorker length outside off and he fails to dig it out
fullish in length wide outside off and he drills it down to sweeper cover
comes round the wicket and he fires that full and Hughes drives to deep cover, brings up the 50 stand
opens the face of the bat and runs it down to third man for a single
tries to steer that past backward point but can't beat the fielder and it's drinks
nearly edges it! Marsh was trying to cut, cramped him up, the ball skids through and falls in the keeper's gloves
edged and that may have been a chance! Outside off, tries to cut and gets a top edge that beats slip and the fielder does well to chase and pull it back before the rope
stays back and punches it to the off side
not the best piece of fielding! Short outside off and he reaches out and slashes it just wide of Darren Bravo at short third man
goes back and chops it to the off side
shuffles and clips him down to midwicket for a couple
angles wide across the left-hander and he watchfully leaves it to the keeper
that was a very half hearted appeal for a caught behind, Hughes tried to run that down to third man, no room at all for that shot, close to the edge

Pollard the juggler! After surviving an appeal for a caught behind Hughes tries to slash this one away wide of backward point on the front foot, flies off the bat and Pollard leaps like a goalkeeper, the ball lobs up and he keeps his eyes on it and takes the catch on the second attempt
stays back and he punches it to the off side
inside edge to the on side and they hesitate, Marsh has to scamper home for the second run and the throw is wide
tossed up outside off and defended
stays back and punches it to the on side
tossed up and he comes forward and punches it to the off side
on the pads and tucked away just wide of short leg
stays back at the crease and defends back to the bowler
comes forward and pushes it to the off side
edged! This one skids through and Marsh gets an outside edge that drops short of slip and goes between keeper and slip
slices it straight to  a diving Pollard at backward point
nips back in and he gets across and knocks it to the off side
drifts on the pads and he turns the face of the bat and works it down to mid-on
the shot he was attempting the previous ball, another half volley drifting on the pads and he turns the face of the bat and works it wide of midwicket this time
drifts on the pads again and he works it away down to fine leg this time
full on the pads and worked to mid-on
Dropped  by Sammy at slip! Round the wicket and angling wide of the off stump, finds the edge off the drive, Sammy moves to his left but fails to hang on, he had to be quicker than that
comes forward and pushes it to the off side
gets forward and punches it
drifts on middle and he works it to the on side
on the leg stump and he works it to the on side
good length outside off and he punches it to the off side
good length outside off and he steers it down to third man for a single
half volley on middle and leg and he punches it firmly down the ground, misfield by the bowler
strays on the pads and he works it behind square on the on side
stays beside the line and he steers it wide of point
full on the off stump and pushed to the off side
beaten on the cut again! Narine's been so unlucky, Marsh cramped for room
stays back and clips it to the on side
risks slicing it and he manages to beat slip
comes round the wicket to Voges, plonks forward and defends
goes back and knocks it towards short leg, not sure what they were appealing for

excellent catch by Thomas! Loose shot by Marsh, this was full and moving away, Marsh slashing away from the body on the front foot, thick outside edge, Thomas decides to do the honours and not leave it to Sammy at slip, throws himself to his left and takes it, 150 wickets in ODIs for "Johnny" Bravo
fullish outside off and driven down to the off side
full outside off and he drives wide of mid-off and Haddin off the mark
fullish on the pads and he clips it to the on side
slower ball but that's far too wide of the off stump
good length on the off stump and he stays right back at the crease and defends
Haddin tries to launch that over cover, gets the elevation but  not the timing, the ball lands well in front of the rope
stays back and he clips it to the on side
goes back at the crease and punches it to the off side
stays back at the crease and knocks it to the on side
drifts down the leg side and it clips the pads and then the keeper
goes back and punches it down the track
starts off the new spell at 140.1 kph, on the pads and tucked to the on side
goes back at the crease and punches it down the track
shuffles back at the crease and he works it down to midwicket, takes a quick single
147.5 kph, sharp bouncer and Haddin did well to hop and fend it off to the on side
fullish on the pads and he works it away to the on side
hops at the crease and pulls on one leg down to deep midwicket
hits a good length on middle and leg and he stays back and defends

nearly a run-out! Voges gets a leading edge to the off side and there's hesitation from both batsmen, somebody had to take a call on the run, they go through with it, Pollard dives and underarms the throw to the bowler's end but nobody backing up, Voges was nowhere close
mistimes the drive back to the bowler
stays beside the line and steers it to the off side
moves across his stumps and knocks it softly towards mid-on and calls early this time
wasted delivery, bouncer down the leg side and Thomas leaps and can't take it cleanly, lobs off his gloves and they take a run as well
stays back and defends back to the bowler
slower ball and he smashes it back down the track and hits the stumps at the other end, had Best got a hand to it...you never know
stays beside the line and he steers it to the off side
this time he drifts wide down the leg side, wasted delivery again
147.8 kph, angles it towards the pads and he works it down to midwicket
shuffles at the crease and knocks it to the on side, they take a couple and finally Australia reach the 100 mark
not the best over for West Indies, this was short and Voges had enough time to rocks back and across and pull that in front of square, the fielder gives chase at deep midwicket
back to back fours, good length on the off stump and Haddin goes for forehand over mid-on, clears the fielder
even better than the previous one! This was fuller and Haddin lofts through the line and gets further elevation over mid-on
stays back and defends back to the bowler, all quiet all of a sudden
on the pads and he works it away down to deep square leg
doesn't give him much room, he taps it to the off side
goes for the slash and it rolls to Best at third man
on target straightaway, on the off stump and he knocks it back down the track
144.6 kph, lovely shot! Mid-on was up, Voges knew that, it was drifting on the pads, turned the face of the bat slightly and made sure he timed it well past the fielder at mid-on
on the pads and he works it behind square on the on side
stays back at the crease and he defends to the off side
pushes it towards mid-off, hesitation in the running but they make it
short outside off and he punches it down to cover
short and wide outside the off stump and he slashes it down to third man
stays back at the crease and punches him to the off side
class! Haddin's shots down the ground have been superb, pitched up on middle and off and he lofts through the line and comfortably clears mid-on
works it away down to midwicket, these two are going at six an over
forces it just wide of mid-on and the fielder dives and stops it
punches it down the track and Sammy does well to slide and cut it off
good length on the off stump and pushed back to the bowler
drives towards cover on the back foot
works it away down to square leg for a single
fullish delivery and punched back to the bowler
this was short and he swivels and pulls him down to fine leg
fullish outside the off stump and he drives him down to cover
comes forward and punches this one to long-on
drifts on the pads and he works it down to mid-on
gives him width outside off and he works it down to third man
drifts on the pads and he works it down to deep square leg
stays back at the crease and mistimes the pull down to midwicket
good length on middle and off and he comes across and defends
nudges it off the pads to the on side
bit of extra bounce and he steers it away down to the off side
drifts on the pads and he fails to time it past the infield
hits his pads and rolls to the off side and there's hesitation in the running, Pollard misses the stumps
full on the off stump and he works it away down to long-on
stays a bit low and he gets a bottom edge on the pull to the on side
pushes it through quicker and he drives back to the bowler
drifts on the pads and he works it down to midwicket
keeps a touch low and he knocks it down to mid-on
the doosra this time, he punches it to the off side
clears the infield! It was pitched up and slightly wide outside off and he made room and carved it over mid-off and cover
short and wide outside off and Voges rocks back and slashes it wide of cover point, nicely timed
Best is struggling already in this spell, drifts wide down the leg side and Voges fails to put it away
hits a good length outside off and he goes back and steers it to the off side
fires that full and wide outside the off stump and he drives him down to deep point
Voges slices that wide of backward point and he brings up his fifty! Makes good use of this opportunity
drifts on the pads and he knocks it towards square leg
comes well forward and defends down the track
fuller in length and he comes well forward and drives towards long-off
on the pads and he turns it down to square leg
the doosra, he pushes it softly to the off side, Thomas runs across and throws to the bowler's end and Narine doesn't even bother getting behind the stumps, Haddin was in trouble
tucks it away behind square on the on side for a single
loosener on middle and off and he pulls him down to long-on
fails to put away a half volley on the pads, hits the legs and rolls away
attempted yorker, clips away the low full toss wide of midwicket
drills a full ball down the ground down to long-on
full on the pads and he works it away down to deep midwicket
top placement from Haddin! It was a slower ball and he read it well, leaned into a half volley and placed it just wide of mid-off
stays back at the crease and knocks it down to third man
goes back and tucks it away down to midwicket
spins back in and he does well to get behind the line and defend
pushes it away softly towards cover and sets off for a single
this was shorter and bashed down to long-off

how did that miss the stumps? Looks like WI are reviewing a lbw appeal, pitched in line with the off stump, comes in with the angle, misses the edge and hits the back pad and clears the stumps, Reiffel signalled byes and Sammy reckoned it was hitting the stumps, Eagle Eye says that was clipping the top of the stumps but too marginal, fair call by the umpire, it's a leg bye since it clipped the pad
good length on middle and worked down to long-on
he opens the face of the bat and runs it down to third man
fullish on the pads and he clips it away down to deep midwicket
finds the gap again! This was short and a touch wide outside off, stays beside the line and slices it wide of backward point
"He's gone long, he's gone high, he's gone all the way has he?" I'll let Bill Lawry do the honours, pitched up on middle and leg and launched just over wide long-on, top shot
full on middle and leg and clipped to long-on
stays beside the line and he knocks it to the off side
outside edge! Haddin wanted to work it to the on side, swings and gets a outside edge that lobs down to third man
exactly the shot he was attempting the previous ball, tried to launch this one over the on side, pulls and miscues it to Powell running forward from deep square leg
Faulkner didn't really see that one, was outside the off stump and he doesn't offer a shot
drifts on the body and he works it behind square on the on side for a couple
comes forward and across his stumps and pushes it to the off side
slower delivery and he opens the face of the bat and runs it down to short third man
lobs it full on middle and leg and he drills it down to long-on
slower ball and he's beaten on the forward prod
loosener on the body and he works it down to short fine leg and that's Australia's 200
punches it in front of deep midwicket and they think of a single
poor delivery by Roach, short on the body with the fine leg up, the batsman helps himself to a pull down to fine leg
tries to pull again but mistimes it back to the bowler
works it away down to midwicket and Darren Bravo slides and misfields, kicks it away towards mid-on
short again and pulled this time along the ground down to deep square leg

makes room and thrashes this one down to Sammy at mid-off who fumbles slightly, been called a no-ball because Faulkner told the umpire that there were only four fielders inside the circle instead of five
on the body and tucked away to the on side
short of a length and he steers it to the off side for a single
that was full and wide and he reaches out and gets a thick outside edge that just beats Roach at short third man, he chases and fails to pull it back, hits the fence
full on the off stump and pushed back to the bowler
just opens the face of the bat and steers it just wide of the keeper, short third man cuts it off
classic cut from Voges, this was wide outside off, he sliced it past the gap between point and short third man
stays back and punches it to the off side
this one skids through and keeps a touch low, he slashes and misses
Best not quite as effective as in his first spell, starts off with a half volley outside off and he leans forward and drives effortlessly wide of mid-off, goes to the 90s
fullish on the pads and he works it away down to midwicket, runs coming too easily
streaky! Faulkner makes a bit of room, the ball was rearing up and he adjusted well and upper cut it over the keeper, Thomas didn't know where that was going
Best is leaking them, this time he strays on the pads and he tucks it away off his pads and it rolls towards fine leg
makes room and drills a full delivery to long-on
drifts on the pads and he works it off the legs to the on side
slower ball short and wide outside off and he slaps that down to cover and there's a fumble, West Indies looking a bit weary here
slower ball on the pads and he works it down to long-on
round the wicket and he drills a half volley down the ground down to long-on
half volley on the pads and worked down to deep midwicket, excellent running by Faulkner as he pushes for the second
makes a bit of room and steers it down to point
attempts a fast yorker and he hammers a low full toss down to long-on
West Indies getting sloppier in the field, this was pulled away and racing towards deep midwicket, Powell runs to his left and tries to boot it away, the ball deflects and hits the rope
that's a century for Voges! On the body and clipped away wide of square leg, he runs the first hard and puts pressure on the fielders for the second, gets home comfortably, 100 off 97 balls!
makes room and the ball hits his pads and rolls to the off side, hitting him well outside leg, a desperate Best appeals
on the pads and he works it behind square leg
makes room and pulls a length delivery down to long-on
slower delivery and he flat-bats that down to long-on
bangs it in short and he makes room and flat-bats it in the air down to long-on, Pollard runs across and cuts it off
another forehand down the ground to long-on, no this is not the Rod Laver arena
fires that fuller and he clips it down to deep square leg, dives at the crease for the second
he makes room and walks across his stumps, the ball just sneaks past the leg stump, should have put that away
bit short outside off and he hammers it down to sweeper cover
Best starts off with a low full toss towards leg and he makes room and hammers it down to long-on
149.4kph, that reached the keeper in a flash, the batsman made room and swished at thin air
clean as a whistle! That was just as quick as the previous ball, made himself room and lofted him downtown flat over long-on
Slower ball and Voges swings too early and misses

makes room and swings and gets an outside edge that runs down to third man, Roach fires the throw to the keeper and Thomas makes the mistake of breaking the stumps with his boot! He then hits the stumps with the glove with ball in hand and Faulkner short of the crease but you can't give that out
makes room and pushes it down to mid-off to end the innings

inn2.comm: on middle and leg and he clips it down to square leg for a single
good delivery, in the channel outside the off stump and it just beats the batsman
stays beside the line and cuts him to the off side
he gets beside the line and gets an inside edge to the pads as he tries to cut
this was dug in short down the leg side, Charles tries to pull but wide called
good length on the off stump and he comes across and knocks it to the on side
opens the face of the bat and he runs it down to third man
lands it outside the off stump and it holds its line before reaching the keeper
close call for Charles! This was short and he didn't quite see it, withdraws the shot and the ball hits his chest and lobs to the off side
gets his bat down and digs out a yorker
gives him width outside off and he cuts it away wide of backward point, the fielders do well to save the boundary

slip catching practice anyone? Tame dismissal, this was short and outside off, Powell could have left it but poked his bat out and tried to angle it past the slips, Finch cups it above his head at second slip
bowls that wide outside the off stump and he doesn't offer a shot
comes forward and across and pushes it to the off side
good length on middle and off and he comes back and across and defends
bashed away! This was a fraction too short, swivels and clubs it behind square on the on side
good length outside off and he comes across and pushes it to the off side
outside edge, he deliberately runs that down to third man
stays over the wicket, lands it outside off and Bravo shoulders arms
keeps it outside the off stump and he comes across and leaves it alone
145.6 kph, similar delivery, keeps it outside off and holds its line before reaching the keeper
143 kph, awkwardly fends it off to the off side, didn't read the length well enough
short of a length and he stays back and taps it down to point
fullish delivery and he comes forward and pushes it to the off side
Charles leaves this alone to the keeper, no swing yet for Mitch
lands it on a good length on the off stump and he drives down the pitch
goes for the flashy off drive, it was full and moving away and he nearly offered an edge to the slips
good length on the pads and he works it away down to fine leg
Charles moves across and comes a few paces forward, changes his mind and checks his shot to the on side
goes for the slash and misses, the ball skids through quicker
Dropped by Finch at second slip! Charles gets an outside edge on the drive and the ball dips low towards second slip, Finch had that covered but the ball slipped out
stays beside the line and pushes it to the off side
147 kph, gives him a bit of width and he drives straight to cover point
this one sneaks past the edge as well, tries to steer it to the off side and the ball just passes the face of the bat
bangs it in short and he swivels and pulls along the ground to fine leg
bangs it in short down the leg side, he shoulders arms
this was down the leg side as well but not called a wide because it was very close to the glove
short delivery and he ducks under that one
stays back and defends down the track
tries to steer that through the off side but ends up chopping it to point
fullish in length outside the off stump and he drives him through the gap at cover
poor bowling, he drifts on the pads with the short fine leg in, just a gentle tickle and it races away for four
close call! He tapped it towards cover and set off, Bravo had to hurry and the underarm throw by Coulter-Nile was just wide of the stumps
lovely shot, this was short outside the off stump and he stays back and punches it wide of cover and point
angles it across the right-hander and he nearly gets an edge
stays behind the line and softly pushes it to the off side
this was angling across him and he chased it, not too far from the edge there
much better this time, it was pitched up and straightening and Charles decides to leave it alone
this was full and wide and deserving to be hit, he comes forward and gets a thick outside edge to third man
comes round the wicket to Bravo, he gets across and defends to the off side
hits a good length on the off stump, Charles taps it to the off side
excellent fielding again! Charles had some width and he pushed it past cover point and two fielders gave chase, Coulter-Nile pulled it back before the rope and Marsh did the rest
good length on middle and leg and he tucks it down to fine leg
fullish on the off stump and he softly pushes it to the off side
turns at the crease and works it to the leg side but can't get it past short  fine leg
gets across and pushes it just to mid-off's left, pinches a single
clean hit, this was short and Charles did well to stay back and control the pull wide of square leg, times it well and finds the gap too
142 kph, this was short too and he sliced it down to third man, controlled shot
short of a length and he stays beside the line and pushes it to the off side
gets across his stumps and pushes a full delivery down to mid-off
pitched up and he tries to go over the top but places it wide of third man, not where he intended, Cutting cuts it off (pun unintended)
stays back at the crease and knocks it to the off side
fullish in length outside the off stump and pushed towards the off side
pushes a full delivery down to mid-off, they take a single
fullish in length outside off and he punches it down to extra cover
goes back at the crease and knocks it to the on side
drifts back in and he works it away to the on side
works it away to the on side
short and wide and he went for a slash and for a few seconds Australia thought they had him, missed the bat
136 kph, stays behind  the line and he works it back to the bowler
goes back at the crease and works it to the on side
pokes his bat out at one that moves across, not far from the edge
stays beside the line and chops it to the off side
clips it away behind square on the on side
short of a length on middle and off and he stays back and defends this one
tossed up and he tucks it off his pads, may have pitched outside leg, the ball straightened
tossed up from round the wicket, clips it to the on side for a single
chips down the track and works it away wide of midwicket
fires that flatter and he drives him hard down to sweeper cover
slower through the air and he clips it away off his pads to short fine leg
tosses it up and he reaches forward and scoops it over cover
good length wide outside off and he cuts him hard but there's protection in the deep
tries to force that away wide of mid-on but he mistimes it
pushes a half volley outside off and down to mid-off
bangs it in short this time and he gets under it very quickly
stays back and he works it wide of midwicket
knocks it in front of midwicket and takes a quick single
skids through and he works it to the on side
goes on the back foot and punches it wide of cover
comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler
flatter delivery and he knocks it down to square leg
comes forward and gets a leading edge that drops safe
stays back and pushes it to the off side
bangs in the bouncer this time but it's down the leg side and he's penalised for it
tempts him with width and Bravo goes for the booming cover drive but misses
this was in the channel outside off and it completely beat him, first slip got a bit excited
stays back at the crease and angles this one down to third man, safely played
stays back at the crease and angles it down to third man
poor ball to end the over, drifts on the pads and he shuffles and works it down to fine leg, well clear of the fielder
tossed up and he comes forward works it to deep square leg
tossed up and he plonks forward and defends
flatter delivery and he works it down to square leg
pushes it down to cover point for a quick single
flatter delivery and he defends to the off side
clips his pads but going down leg
a touch risky! This was wide outside off and slashed just over the leaping backward point
full and pushes it through the line just wide of mid-off
good length outside off and he punches it down to backward point
tries the yorker and he comes forward and jams it out just wide of extra cover
stays on the back foot and he punches it wide of point
bowls it full and wide and he can't resist the lofted drive, good enough for a couple as the sweeper cuts it off
tosses it up and he thrashes it straight to mid-off
bang! Doherty tosses it up and Bravo charges down the pitch scoops it high over mid-off, rocketed away
drifts down the leg side and wide called
bowls it flatter and he stays back and cuts him to deep point
fuller delivery and drilled down the ground to long-off
comes forward and defends to the off side
tossed up and he works it with the turn to long-on
bangs it in short and down the leg side and he ducks under it
short on the body and he hops back and softly tucks it towards fine leg, they take the first quickly
pitched up and he goes for the drive, good delivery, straightens and nearly takes the outside edge
good length on middle and leg and he stays back and defends
good length on middle and leg and he works it away down to mid-on
good length outside off and he safely dabs this one down to third man to bring up his fifty! He has looked quite composed
tossed up and he comes forward and defends
close call for Charles! He chips down the track and lofts down to wide long-on, Faulkner was far too forward from the rope and the ball just cleared him
pushes it to the off side
now he chips down the track and goes for the slog and mistimes it
fired full and flat outside off and he drives hard, misfield at short cover
drops it with soft hands towards the off side

Appeal for a caught behind and the umpire shakes his head! Australia are reviewing it. It was short and Charles was looking to pull, the ball certainly hit his arm, Hot Spot showed a slight edge off the bat before hitting the arm, but Charles gets the benefit of the doubt! Was the Hot Spot not conclusive enough?
attempts the shot again, this was short and pulled along the ground, deep square leg cuts it off
see you downtown! This was a length delivery and Charles used the crease and swung his arms, connected cleanly and sent it over wide long-on
shot! This was short and wide and he slashed at it and sent it wide and safe of backward point
dabs it toward short third man for a single
tossed up and he comes forward and defends
close call! Tucked to the leg side, Haddin gathered and had a shy at the stumps at his end and missed

fine catch by Faulkner! Doherty tossed it up from round the wicket, Bravo was down the track looking to force it flat past mid-off, Faulkner moved quickly to his right and took the catch inches from the ground on the dive
clips it away towards square leg for a single
stays back and slashes it down to short third man
comes round the wicket and he blocks it to the off side
stays beside the line and he steers it to the off side
streaky shot by Bravo as he leans forward and checks his drive wide of cover, in the air but in the gap
angles it from round the wicket and he works it to the leg side
close call for Bravo as he gets one that  rears up from outside off, he goes for the slash but doesn't have any room for the shot
stays beside the line and knocks it to the covers
gets on his knee and sweeps to the leg side
missed stumping! Charles was down the pitch and yorked himself, Haddin didn't see it at all
pushes it to the off side
goes on the back foot and punches it wide of cover
this one straightens and just sneaks past the inside edge
flatter delivery and clipped to the on side
that's a big bouncer and he's penalised for it
Hughes drops a skier! Bravo took his hand off the bat and skied that miles in the air, didn't control it, Hughes was moving to his right at cover, somehow lost it in the lights
and follows that up with a six! All happening here, it was pitched up and he went forward and lofted it over long-off
quite an eventful over! Mitchell Johnson fires that full from round the wicket, angles it towards the stumps, Bravo plays down the wrong line and is bowled through the gate
143 kph, thudded into Haddin's gloves, Pollard doesn't offer a shot
144 kph, this was closer to the off stump and he leaves it alone
flatter delivery and he pushes it back to the bowler
fullish on the stumps and he drives down  the ground to long-on
tossed up and he comes well forward and drives to mid-off
gets well forward and drives him to mid-on
Charles soldiers on, tossed up and full outside off, he leans forward and smashes it past short cover
Pollard gently pushes it to the off side, sets off and heads back
bangs it in short and it's the slower bouncer, he ducks under it
stays back and punches it towards cover
sharp single, he was on the back foot to punch it towards mid-off and set off immediately, the fielder couldn't gather quickly enough
picks it from outside off and goes for the slog but mistimes it
end the over with a bouncer, Pollard safely ducks under it
good length on the off stump and he stabs it back to the bowler
the slower ball and he didn't pick it well, slashes and misses
the substitute Carters drops a sitter! This was pitched up and lofted towards sweeper cove and the fielder had it covered but somehow the ball slipped out

Appeal for an lbw and Charles has been given out and he reviews it! It pitched in line and straightened and replays showed an inside edge, the doubt was also whether the ball brushed the front pad before hitting the edge, not conclusive enough, Charles survives. What a night he's having!
leans forward and gets an outside edge wide of point
nothing's stopping Charles tonight! This was full and wide outside off, he reaches out and drives and gets an outside edge past the keeper, no slip
short outside off and he slashes and misses
another slash and a miss! This was closer to the off stump, Charles on the edge
gets beside the line and he slices him wide of backward point
drifts on the pads and he tucks it to the leg side
stays back and stabs it down the ground to long-on
overthrows! Punched towards mid-off, they set off and Charles is sent back, Doherty hits the stumps and they take a run off the ricochet
stays back and pulls just wide of short midwicket for a couple, managed to find the gap
on the off stump and he defended it to the off side
Pollard's first boundary! This was short outside the off stump and he stayed back, swiveled and pulled in front of square, found the gap well
stays right back at the crease and defends to the off side
full and wide outside the off stump and he reaches out and gets an outside edge down to third man
good length outside off and punched down to cover
stays back at the crease and knocks it down to mid-on, the field's up
Pollard gets one that rises up a bit and he slashes and misses
persists with that line just outside off, there are fielders in the ring, Pollard punches it straight to short cover
this time he stands tall and knocks it just wide of point and takes a sharp single, Johnson dives
exquisite drive straight after drinks! Half volley on the off stump, he leans forward and pushes it through the line and beats mid-off and long-on running across
skids through and hits his pads as he tries to knock it away
stays behind the line and defends back to the bowler
good running, punches it towards mid-off and set off quickly
goes back at the crease and mistimes the punch back to the bowler
bowls that full and wide outside off and he gets forward and drives to sweeper cover
the slower bouncer this time and he fetches it high on the bat and controls the pull down to deep square leg
punched on the up square on the off side and backward point does well to get around and stop it
that's a good delivery and well played, zips towards the legs and he manages to flick it down to fine leg
skids through and he stays behind the line and defends down the track
142 kph, a slash and a miss to keep the Australians interested! Tried to force it through the off side, close to the edge
he bowls it short and it hurries on him, goes for the pull and miscues it but there's nobody at square leg
that was quick and flat, he does well to gt his bat down and defend
slower through the air this time and he drives to the off side
full and wide outside off  and he drives just wide of short cover
this was fired flat and quick and he punches it to mid-on
stays back and knocks it to short cover
stays back and he knocks it down the track
on the body and he clips it away wide of square leg, good running to pick up two
tries to force that through the off side but can't beat mid-off
this was down the leg side, Cutting not controlling his line there
better delivery, it was a bouncer and he quickly ducks under it
stays back and knocks it wide of square leg for a single
slower delivery and he pushes it down to short cover, can't find the gap
he makes a hint of room and tries to steer that past backward point, doesn't get the placement right
fullish in length on the off stump and he drives back to the bowler
shorter on the body and he shuffles and clips it to the leg side
makes a hint of room and pulls along the ground in front of square, picks up a couple
That's Johnson Charles' first century in elite cricket would you believe it! Outside off and he opens the face of the bat and deliberately dabs it wide of the wicketkeeper

goes straight after his century! This was short on the body and he was looking to shuffle across and pull, miscued it and it popped straight to short fine leg, Cutting falls forward and takes the catch
stays back and defends back to the bowler
goes back at the crease and defends back to the bowler
doesn't give him room, he can only knock it to the off side
he's got his eye in now! This was pitched up outside off, cleared his front leg and slammed it over the bowler and mid-on
tried to repeat that boundary! This was closer to the off stump, Deonarine made himself room to smash it down the ground, thin edge to Haddin, WI losing the plot a bit
outside edge and it drops short of first slip! He played it with soft hands and it fell well short of Finch
nervy start for Thomas! He tried to shoulder arms but the ball took the inside edge and rolled to the keeper
the slower ball and he reads it late and gets forward and defends
another slower one and defended and there was the slight danger of the ball rolling back to the stumps, Pollard was alert
keeps it nice and tight, straight on the stumps and Pollard defends
keeps him quiet four balls in a row! Defends with soft hands and the ball nearly dribbled to the stumps again
make that five, another good slower ball, outside off and Pollard decides not to play at it
top over from McKay in the Powerplay, this time it's a single down to square leg
Pollard stays back and swivels and pulls but can't beat mid-on, the fielder's at the edge of the circle
this was fractionally short and he pulls along the ground wide of midwicket, pushes for the second, Thomas dives
drifts on the body and he stays back and clips it wide of square leg
fuller delivery and he leans forward and drills that one down to mid-off and sets off
this one skids through, hits his pads and deflects towards third man, just one run, WI need boundaries
keeps him quiet, tucks him up for room and Thomas is happy to come forward and drive to cover
skids through and he stays back and punches it down to long-on
flatter one on the pads and he can't flick it away
shuffles and knocks it off his pads down to short fine leg
bashes a full delivery down the ground to long-off

Thomas shows Pollard he can do it too! That was too full, on middle and leg and he lofts crisply over wide long-on, at least three spectators wanted it and the lad dropped it
stays back and knocks it down to to the on side and they take a single
good length on the off stump and defended down to cover
this was short and he swivels and pulls down to deep square leg
shuffles at the crease and knocks it down to square leg
ends the over with a bouncer, Pollard was quick to get underneath it

McKay strays down the leg side and wide called, he should be careful since the fine leg is up
mixup! He tucks it down to long-on, they pick up a second and it looked like both batsmen were ball-watching, Pollard dives
steal a sharp single there! Slower ball and he awkwardly fends it off one-handed to the on side, sets off quickly
cleverly done again, he opens the face of the bat and gently steers it wide of short third man for a single
stays back at the crease and pushes it firmly down to long-off
slower ball and driven firmly back to the bowler and McKay slides and fumbles, well they sneak in another single
well played! Johnson fires that from round the wicket, Thomas leans forward, opens the face and deliberately runs it down to third man, no slip
good length on middle and leg and he stays behind the line and defends
good length on the pads and he stays back and clips it to the leg side, Thomas doing this well
pushes it softly down to mid-on and calls quickly for the single
fullish in length outside off and he squirts it just wide of short cover
bowls it short on the body and he stays back and quietly knocks it to the leg side
drifts on the pads and he stylish whips it on the up down to deep square leg

Appeal for a run out and Thomas in the firing line! Squirted down to backward point, Marsh fumbled but gathered quickly and hurled it to the bowler, Thomas was struggling, he dived and his bat was in the air when Faulkner whips off the bails. The bowler did well to get behind the stumps
fuller delivery and he drills it down to long-on
stays back at the crease and he defends down to cover, tells Pollard to stay back
bowls that full outside off and he crunches it down to long-off
slower ball outside off and very tempting for Pollard, he swished at it and missed, the field on the off side is up
stays right back at the crease and he punches it down to cover
drifts on the pads and he shuffles and works it to the on side
this time he pitches it up and goes for the big drive but misses, a dot ball!
Sammy missed out there! Half volley outside off and he can only drill it straight to cover
much better by Sammy as he stabs one down to point and gets off strike
a single is all he will get, pacy delivery on the body and he shuffles and works it wide of Johnson, he keeps the strike though

Pollard goes! Faulkner pitched it up slightly and Pollard was waiting for that length to go for his favourite straight loft, he used the crease but didn't get enough on the shot to clear long-on, Finch was alert
he shuffles and works it to the on side
outside off and he pushes it to the off side
stays on the back foot and punches it to the off side
that's a yorker length which he drills down towards cover, can't do much with that
yet another dot ball! Narine doesn't offer a shot this time, maybe wants to leave the hitting to his captain
Sammy stays back at the crease and just slaps it between mid-off and cover but not good enough for a four
he gets a boundary this time! This was short from round the wicket, stayed at the crease and clubbed it in the air and just wide of deep square leg
targets that boundary again! This was short and he swiveled and pulled this one along the ground to fine leg, 30 off 15
backs away and he drills a full delivery down to mid-off, disappointed he couldn't put that away
hits the leg stump! Narine backs away and exposes his stumps going for the straight hit, Johnson fired that full on the stumps, hits the top of leg, WI eight down
shuffles across and he gets hit on the pads, too quick for him
that's a nasty yorker! Sammy lost his balance and fell over at the crease, managed to flick it to the on side
makes room and crashes a full delivery down to long-off
this one skidded through and beat the bat as he tried to cut, Haddin fails to gather it
makes room and bashes another full delivery down to long-off
shuffles across and Roach tries to clear midwicket but miscues it, no fielders there
Roach tries to swish this away as well and it's a slower ball, swings and misses
Sammy's not done yet! It was a full delivery wide outside off, he made room and smashed that over long-off
is that game over yet? It's a slower ball, back of the hand, Sammy makes room and swings, thin edge down to Haddin
Best wanted to smash that over the on side, instead it lobs to the off side, can';t connect well
slower ball and he swings and misses, Australia are all but through
Best connects alright but it's down to deep midwicket! Big swing, and not enough power on that to carry it over the rope, Coulter-Nile judges it well under the lights. Australia have sealed this 5-0.
